---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro'
import CodeBlock from '../../components/CodeBlock.astro'
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro'
---

<Base title="Introducing Solon — Your AI. Your rules.">
  <Navbar current="/blog" />

  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-16 pb-32">
    <time class="text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">February 2026</time>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight mt-3 mb-8">
      Introducing Solon: Your AI. Your rules.
    </h1>

    <div class="prose text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <p>
        Running AI models locally has gotten easy. Running them <em>securely</em> has not.
      </p>

      <p>
        Over 175,000 Ollama instances are exposed to the internet without any authentication.
        The current default path for self-hosted AI is a security disaster. We built Solon to fix this.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-12 mb-4">What is Solon?</h2>
      <p>
        Solon is a self-hosted AI runtime that combines Ollama-level simplicity with production-grade
        security. It's a single Go binary that runs AI models locally and exposes them via an
        authenticated, OpenAI-compatible API.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-12 mb-4">Security is the foundation</h2>
      <p>
        Auth is mandatory. There is no <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-white/[0.06] px-1 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">--no-auth</code> flag. Every request requires an API key.
        Keys are bcrypt-hashed and shown only once on creation. Rate limiting and audit logging
        are enabled by default.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-12 mb-4">Get started in 30 seconds</h2>
      <CodeBlock code={`# Install
curl -fsSL https://get.solon.dev | sh

# Start (auto-creates your first API key)
solon serve

# Pull a model
solon models pull llama3.2:3b

# Make a request
curl http://localhost:8420/v1/chat/completions \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer sol_sk_live_xxxx" \\
  -d '{"model":"llama3.2:3b","messages":[{"role":"user","content":"Hello!"}]}'`} />

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-12 mb-4">Key features</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
        <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200">Single binary</strong> — No Docker, no Python, no dependencies</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200">OpenAI-compatible</strong> — Works with any existing OpenAI SDK</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200">Mandatory auth</strong> — API keys, rate limiting, audit logging</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200">Secure tunnel</strong> — Expose your API via Cloudflare Tunnel</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200">Web dashboard</strong> — Manage everything from your browser</li>
        <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-200">Model management</strong> — Pull, list, and remove models from the CLI</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-12 mb-4">Open source</h2>
      <p>
        Solon is MIT licensed. The core product is free forever. Revenue comes from optional
        managed infrastructure (Solon Relay for stable URLs) and team features — not from
        artificial limitations on the open-source core.
      </p>

      <p>
        We'd love your feedback. Star us on
        <a href="https://github.com/openclaw/solon" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 hover:underline">GitHub</a>,
        try it out, and let us know what you think.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</Base>
